IRS990.Desc: THE IOWA PBS FOUNDATION EXISTS TO FOSTER GIVING TO IOWA PBS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ACCOUNTING PRINCIPLES GENERALLY ACCEPTED IN THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA REQUIRE MANAGEMENT TO EVALUATE TAX POSITIONS TAKEN BY THE FOUNDATION AND RECOGNIZE A TAX LIABILITY (OR ASSET) FOR AN UNCERTAIN POSITION THAT MORE LIKELY THAN NOT WOULD NOT BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION BY THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE. MANAGEMENT HAS EVALUATED THEIR MATERIAL TAX POSITIONS AND DETERMINED THERE ARE NO UNCERTAIN POSITIONS TAKEN OR EXPECTED TO BE TAKEN THAT WOULD REQUIRE RECOGNITION OF A LIABILITY (OR ASSET) OR DISCLOSURES IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE FOUNDATION IS SUBJECT TO ROUTINE AUDITS BY TAX AUTHORITIES; HOWEVER, THERE ARE CURRENTLY NO AUDITS FOR ANY TAX PERIODS IN PROGRESS. MANAGEMENT BELIEVES THE FOUNDATION IS NO LONGER SUBJECT TO INCOME TAX EXAMINATIONS FOR FISCAL YEARS ENDED PRIOR TO JUNE 30, 2018.
SCHEDULE M COLUMN B REPORTS NUMBER OF DONATIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A COPY OF THE 990 WILL BE SENT TO EACH BOARD MEMBER FOR INDIVIDUAL REVIEW AND COMMENTS ARE SOLICITED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: BOARD MEMBERS COMPLETE CONFLICT OF INTEREST FORMS ANNUALLY. BOARD MEMBERS WILL ABSTAIN FROM VOTES WHERE THEY HAVE A CONFLICT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A COMPENSATION STUDY WAS CONDUCTED BY AN INDEPENDENT FIRM AND PRESENTED TO MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS IN DETERMINING THE BASE COMPENSATION FOR THE TOP MANAGEMENT OFFICIAL. THE COMPENSATION STUDY WAS CONDUCTED IN 2020. A COMPENSATION STUDY WILL BE PERFORMED EVERY THREE TO FIVE YEARS OR AS DETERMINED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.
